Liz,

(scroll down for the important part)

I'm pulling together the pieces. The JSONP file we're talking about is http://www.london2012.com/js/linkdata.js (slightly updated now with correct mascot link).

Cogapp described what needs to be done to implement it on a 3rd party website in their email "Fwd: Success! We now have one solution for ANY domain.", dated 7 April, as follows:

-----------
From: Martin Edwards <martined@cogapp.com>
Some techie info for Jamie.

The microsite content I delivered contained this code below (which linked to a PHP script):

       $.getJSON("http://www.london2012.com/js/linkdata.js", function(data){
               $.each(data.links.link, function(){
                       $("div.drop-down ul").append('<li><a href="' + $(this).attr("url") + '">' + $(this).attr("name") + '</a></li>');
               });     
       });

That should be changed to this one line (replacing the URL with the final LOCOG location):

       $.getJSON("http://www.cogapp.com/temp/locog/json/links-list.js?callback=?");

In the cross domain JavaScript file (attached) you'll see we've wrapped the JSON content in a JavaScript function "linkData":



When this content is returned the "linkData" function is instantly picked up by the code below and outputs the link options in the drop down:

       function linkData(data) {
               $.each(data.links.link, function(){
                       $("div.drop-down ul").append('<li><a href="' + $(this).attr("url") + '">' + $(this).attr("name") + '</a></li>');
               });
       }

Let me know if you've got any queries.

Martin Edwards
Front End Web Developer

Tel No: (01273) 821600
Fax: (01273) 728866
---------

But then we asked if it's okay if we implement it with a fixed callback, and cogapp nodded, but hasn't produced a modified code. Here's a modified version.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="">
<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<title></title>
</head>
<body>
<script type="text/javascript" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.4/jquery.min.js"></script>
<div class="drop-down">
<ul>
</ul>
</div>

<script>
	linkData = function(data) {
		$.each(data.links.link, function(){
			$("div.drop-down ul").append('<li><a href="' + $(this).attr("url") + '">' + $(this).attr("name") + '</a></li>');
		});
	}
</script>

... site body ...

<script src="http://www.london2012.com/js/linkdata.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
